      "content": "\"the data overwhelmingly supports it\" sounds pretty definitive. but what about the people who argue that focusing on the 'long-term societal costs' just ignores the immediate reality for people living paycheck to paycheck? like, if a nurse or a delivery driver can't afford the toll, does the 'public health saving' actually matter to them? doesn't that make the policy inherently unfair regardless of the environmental data?",
