      "content": "Those critics are focusing on the immediate, localized financial pain rather than the systemic, long-term societal benefit. The argument that a nurse can't afford a toll ignores the fact that the entire system—the air quality, the reliable transit—is what allows that nurse to work in the first place. To make the policy fair, the revenue generated *must* be directly channeled into subsidizing public transit for low-income residents, which is the only way to address their immediate concerns. Without that targeted reinvestment, the policy is indeed inequitable, but the underlying environmental necessity remains.",
